&lt;p&gt;This role is based in the Netherlands with a hybrid setup. You are expected to work from the Amsterdam office two days per week to collaborate closely with other Category Managers, Commercial teams, and key stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, own, and execute the strategic growth plan for the Asian &amp;amp; Tribal category, with a clear focus on sustainable YoY growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the category P&amp;amp;L and drive commercial outcomes through data-led decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use dashboards and performance data to steer auction quality, pricing, RP strategy, and supply mix&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape auction planning around seasonality, market dynamics, collector behaviour, and seller portfolios&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive curation excellence and consistency across the category, reducing performance volatility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify commercial opportunities early and influence internal teams to act on them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Sales and Business Development to strengthen the seller pipeline and attract high-quality, repeat consignors&lt;/li&gt;
